cartilage parallel to the helix","A curved rim forming the outer border of the auricle","A small cartilaginous projection anterior to the external acoustic meatus","A lobule of soft tissue at the inferior portion of the ear"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etragus is a small cartilaginous projection that extends anteriorly over the external acoustic meatus\u003C/strong\u003E. It serves as a protective structure and aids in sound localisation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecurved rim forming the outer border of the auricle\u003C/strong\u003E describes the helix, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Edepression in the central portion of the external ear\u003C/strong\u003E describes the concha. The \u003Cstrong\u003Efold of cartilage parallel to the helix\u003C/strong\u003E describes the antihelix, and the \u003Cstrong\u003Elobule of soft tissue at the inferior portion of the ear\u003C/strong\u003E describes the earlobe. The tragus is an important anatomical landmark when examining the external ear and can be used as a reference point when performing otoscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The tragus is a small cartilaginous projection that extends anteriorly over the external acoustic meatus of the ear.","The tragus helps protect the external acoustic meatus and aids in sound localisation."],"references":["Bahrani B, Khachemoune A. Review of accessory tragus with highlights of its associated syndromes. Int J Dermatol. 2014 Dec;53(12):1442-6. doi: 10.1111/ijd.12369. Epub 2014 Sep 30. PMID: 25266223.","Heine PA. Anatomy of the ear. Vet Clin North Am Small Anim Pract. 2004 Mar;34(2):379-95. doi: 10.1016/j.cvsm.2003.10.003. PMID: 15062614.","Szymanski A, Geiger Z. Anatomy, Head and Neck, Ear. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions